result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffrey Andre Love was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Armed Robbery with Threat of Force [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).
  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jeffrey Andre Love in court with attorney Victoria Mccandless.  Defendant Jeffrey Andre Love in custody.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for Ron Dague for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk 
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

As to Count 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 18 YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 8 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.
As to Count 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS CONCURRENT to Count 1. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.
These sentences are CONCURRENT any other sentence.  Defendant has 259 days credit.
Court finds defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and IS ELIGIBLE the WI Substance Abuse program.  
Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
- Cooperate with the Probation Department
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute/maintain sobriety, no alcohol, no drugs.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol. No possession of drug paraphernalia
- Random urine screens.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation.
- No contact with: Atomic Glass, Patrick M or Louis E
- Provide a DNA sample.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Pay the DNA surcharges
-  No Cash Bail Posted in this matter (OR Cash bail on deposit to be applied.)  
-  Court ordered that all other court costs, fines, surcharges be waived due the defendant's circumstances.  DNA surcharges be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm. 
Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
Court advised defendant that he may not vote until his civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Jeffrey Andre Love in court with attorney Victoria Mccandless.  Defendant Jeffrey Andre Love in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  As to both counts:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
Defendant is ordered to provide a DNA sample.   Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 19.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 28, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
